The '''Emily M. Gray Award''' from the [[Biophysical Society]] in [[Rockville, Maryland]], is given in recognition of "significant contributions to education in biophysics."<ref name="awardsite">[http://www.biophysics.org/AwardsOpportunities/SocietyAwards/EmilyMGrayAward/tabid/500/Default.aspx Emily M. Gray Award page] (last visited Mar. 24, 2014).</ref> The award was established in 1997 and first awarded the year thereafter.
== Award recipients ==
* 1998: [[Muriel S. Prouty]] * 1999: [[Kensal E. van Holde]] * 2000: [[Charles Cantor]] and [[Paul Schimmel]] * 2001: [[Jane S. Richardson|Jane Richardson]] * 2002: [[Norma Allewell]] * 2003: Michael Summers * 2004: [[Richard D. Ludescher]] * 2005: [[Barry R. Lentz]] * 2006: [[Ignacio Tinoco, Jr.]] * 2007: [[John Steve Olson]]<ref>[http://news.rice.edu/2006/08/31/rice-biochemist-honored-by-biophysical-society/ Rice biochemist honored by biophysical society]</ref> * 2008: [[David Eisenberg|David S. Eisenberg]] and [[Donald Crothers|Donald M. Crothers]]<ref>[http://www.biophysics.org/Portals/1/PDFs/Press%20Room/2007/2008%20Award%20Recipients.pdf Biophysical Society Names 2008 Award Recipients]</ref> * 2009: [[Philip C. Nelson]]<ref>[http://www.biophysics.org/Portals/1/PDFs/Press%20Room/2008/2009%20Society%20Awards%20press%20release2.pdf Biophysical Society Announces 2009 Distinguished Service and Emily M. Gray Award Recipients as well as Society Fellows]</ref> * 2010: [[Greta Pifat-Mrzljak]]<ref>[http://www.biophysics.org/Portals/1/PDFs/Press%20Room/2010/2010%20Society%20Awards%20press%20release.pdf Biophysical Society Names 2010 Award Recipients]</ref> * 2011: [[Bertil Hille]]<ref>[http://www.biophysics.org/Portals/1/PDFs/Press%20Room/2010/2011%20Society%20Awards%20Press%20release.pdf Biophysical Society Names 2011 Award Recipients]</ref> * 2012: [[Ken A. Dill|Kenneth Dill]] and [[Sarina Bromberg]]<ref>[http://www.biophysics.org/Portals/1/PDFs/Press%20Room/2011/2012%20emily%20gray%20and%20distinguished%20service%20release%20%20ltrhd.pdf Biophysical Society Names 2012 Distinguished Service and Emily Gray Awardees]</ref> * 2013: [[Louis de Felice]]<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.biophysics.org/Portals/1/Society%20awards%202012%20release%202.pdf|title = Biophysical Society Names 2013 Distinguished Service and Emily M. Gray Awardees|date = |accessdate = |website = |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref> * 2014: Alberto Diaspro<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.biophysics.o